        <argsstring>() const =0</argsstring>
        <name>getActor</name>
        <qualifiedname>endstone::DamageSource::getActor</qualifiedname>
        <briefdescription>
<para>Get the actor that caused the damage to occur. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>Not to be confused with <ref refid="classendstone_1_1DamageSource_1aaffa76098f44b6d00d74775316c05139" kindref="member">DamageSource::getDamagingActor()</ref>, the returned actor is the actor to which the damage is ultimately attributed if the receiver is killed. If, for example, the receiver was damaged by a projectile, the shooter/thrower would be returned.</para>
<para><simplesect kind="return"><para>an <ref refid="classendstone_1_1Actor" kindref="compound">Actor</ref>, or a null handle if none. </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
        </detaileddescription>
        <inbodydescription>
        </inbodydescription>
