        <argsstring>() const =0</argsstring>
        <name>getDamagingActor</name>
        <qualifiedname>endstone::DamageSource::getDamagingActor</qualifiedname>
        <briefdescription>
<para>Get the actor that directly caused the damage. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>Not to be confused with <ref refid="classendstone_1_1DamageSource_1a4db47c0262336513f37cb47c7bac0b73" kindref="member">DamageSource::getActor()</ref>, the returned actor is the actor that actually inflicted the damage. If, for example, the receiver was damaged by a projectile, the projectile would be returned.</para>
<para><simplesect kind="return"><para>an <ref refid="classendstone_1_1Actor" kindref="compound">Actor</ref>, or a null handle if none. </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
